ðŸ“˜ Problem Statement

Kathir is learning about Binary Search Trees (BST) in his computer science class. 
He has implemented a program to construct a BST by inserting integers and then 
calculate the sum of all leaf nodes in the tree.
The input ends when -1 is encountered. The program should compute and display the 
sum of all leaf nodes present in the BST.


---

ðŸ“¥ Input Format

The input consists of a series of positive integers, each on a separate line.

Input terminates when -1 is entered.

All input integers are unique.



---

ðŸ“¤ Output Format

Print the sum of all leaf nodes in the BST in the format:
Sum of all leaf nodes are X



---

ðŸ“Œ Code Constraints

All input integers are positive.

Number of nodes â‰¤ 100.

Value of each node â‰¤ 100.



---

ðŸ§ª Sample Test Case 1

Input

5
3
7
2
4
9
-1

Output

Sum of all leaf nodes are 15


---

ðŸ§ª Sample Test Case 2

Input

6
3
1
4
2
-1

Output

Sum of all leaf nodes are 6


---

 C++ Code 

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

struct node {
    int data;
    struct node* left;
    struct node* right;
};

struct node* root = NULL;

struct node* createNode(int d) {
    struct node* newnode = (struct node*)malloc(sizeof(struct node));
    newnode->data = d;
    newnode->left = NULL;
    newnode->right = NULL;
    return newnode;
}

void append(int d) {
    struct node* temp = root;
    struct node* parent = NULL;
    struct node* newnode = createNode(d);

    if (root == NULL) {
        root = newnode;
        return;
    }

    while (temp != NULL) {
        parent = temp;
        if (d < temp->data)
            temp = temp->left;
        else
            temp = temp->right;
    }

    if (d < parent->data)
        parent->left = newnode;
    else
        parent->right = newnode;
}

void leafsum(struct node* root, int* sum) {
    if (root == NULL)
        return;

    if (root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL)
        *sum += root->data;

    leafsum(root->left, sum);
    leafsum(root->right, sum);
}

int main() {
    int d;
    do {
        cin >> d;
        if (d > 0)
            append(d);
    } while (d != -1);

    int sum = 0;
    leafsum(root, &sum);
    cout << "Sum of all leaf nodes are " << sum;
    return 0;
}
